CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 11, 1961, p. 2, reads: "Candidates Work Hard in Victory Quest - GOP Opposition Plots - Lenwood Carpenter, Republican candidate for constable in the 13th Ward, maps strategy with supporters of the 15th and 16th Districts.  He lost to Leo Washington.  Left to right: Garner Little, Louis Pirozzi, Mr. Carpenter, James J. Durzo, Robert L. Carter and an unidentified follower in back row. - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Garner Little, Louis Pirozzi, Lenwood Carpenter, unknown man in back, James J. Durzo, and Robert L. Carter standing on street with Mary's Market in background
